"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-08-08-2024-Olympic-triathlon-gold-medalist-on-Seine-We-swam-in-worse-rivers-1vTxu8j0OlO-p.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 145, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You can change your cookie settings through your browser.\", \"from\": 146, \"to\": 203, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sports Scene  Copied  Cassandre Beaugrand of France displays her women's individual triathlon gold medal at the 2024 Summer Olympics in Paris, France, July 31, 2024.\", \"from\": 205, \"to\": 370, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 250, \"end\": 256, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9959545206198764, \"rank\": 0.0034726261902209214, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 341, \"end\": 346, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999990034212, \"rank\": 9.965254260694005e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 348, \"end\": 354, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9959545206198764, \"rank\": 0.0034726261902209214, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"/CFP  Cassandre Beaugrand of France won the women's individual triathlon gold medal at the 2024 Paris Summer Olympics after competing in the Seine River on July 31.\", \"from\": 371, \"to\": 535, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 377, \"end\": 396, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cassandre_Beaugrand\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cassandre Beaugrand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cassandre_Beaugrand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cassandre_Beaugrand\"}, {\"begin\": 400, \"end\": 406, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9959545206198764, \"rank\": 0.0034726261902209214, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The victory marked her country's first-ever gold in the sport at the Games.\", \"from\": 536, \"to\": 611, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Before the competitions got underway, the Seine fell under scrutiny over its water quality, resulting in the cancellations of multiple swimming practices and a delay.\", \"from\": 613, \"to\": 779, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 655, \"end\": 660, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999997610723598, \"rank\": 1.5404147218725017e-07, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We knew so many people would have asked questions.\", \"from\": 781, \"to\": 832, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So we were prepared for that.\", \"from\": 833, \"to\": 862, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And I will just say, we swam in worse rivers sometimes, like in Tokyo, I do not think it was that great.\", \"from\": 863, \"to\": 967, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 927, \"end\": 932, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9988307614858708, \"rank\": 0.0011699592981433188, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And no one was sick.\", \"from\": 968, \"to\": 988, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We raced in the Seine the year before for the test event, and no one was sick after that,\\\" Beaugrand told reporters.\", \"from\": 989, \"to\": 1105, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1005, \"end\": 1010, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999997610723598, \"rank\": 1.5404147218725017e-07, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"So I knew that we would have actually raced, I was very confident about it,\\\" she added \\\"I was very focused on my race.\", \"from\": 1107, \"to\": 1226, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I think I started knowing that I was racing for the podium when we were in the run, because we were like four girls and I knew that we had a little gap with the others.\", \"from\": 1227, \"to\": 1395, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So I was just trying to grind my teeth and go for it, and just keep believing that I could do it.\\\"\", \"from\": 1396, \"to\": 1494, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Alex Yee of Great Britain won the men's individual event.\", \"from\": 1496, \"to\": 1553, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1496, \"end\": 1504, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Yee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alex Yee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Yee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Yee\"}, {\"begin\": 1508, \"end\": 1521, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.7645385199068618, \"rank\": 0.3078903185027843, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The mixed delay title went to Tim Hellwig, Lisa Tertsch, Lasse Luhrs and Laura Lindemann of Germany.\", \"from\": 1554, \"to\": 1654, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1597, \"end\": 1601, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lisa_Simpson\", \"score\": 0.9999996373772522, \"rank\": 3.240434658011483e-07, \"text\": \"Lisa\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lisa_Simpson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lisa_Simpson\"}, {\"begin\": 1611, \"end\": 1616, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lasse_Holm\", \"score\": 0.9999999999813554, \"rank\": 1.8541819953641527e-11, \"text\": \"Lasse\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lasse_Holm\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lasse_Holm\"}, {\"begin\": 1627, \"end\": 1642, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Lindemann\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Laura Lindemann\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Lindemann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Lindemann\"}, {\"begin\": 1646, \"end\": 1653, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.575072891610007, \"rank\": 0.7379056549505342, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\", \"from\": 1656, \"to\": 1916, \"entities\": []}]}"